results.title: Underground!
results.description: Peter Parker and Joy Mercado, on assignment for the Daily Bugle, find a secret project under the tiny Appalachian town of Temple Corners

results.title: The Magma Solution
results.description: Spider-Man disappears in the aftermath of his explosive battle with Magma

results.title: The Longest Road!
results.description: Peter Parker tells Mary Jane Watson how he got back from Appalachia; on the final page of this story, Peter is pushed in front of a subway train by an unknown person who will eventually be revealed as Venom

results.title: Humbug!
results.description: As Peter Parker prepares for a trip to England, Spider-Man has little trouble dispatching the Humbug

results.title: Treasures!
results.description: The Vulturions apply for the job of the Kingpin's assassins by attempting to kill Spider-Man

results.title: Little Wars!
results.description: While in England, Spider-Man prevents a radical group called the Red Hand from assassinating Margaret Thatcher

results.title: The Enemy Unknown!
results.description: While on a ferry to Ireland, Peter Parker remembers thwarting a Spider-Man imposter several months previously

results.title: Profit of Doom
results.description: Spider-Man learns of Roxxon's plans to sell a super-weapon to the British government

results.title: Slip Slydin' Away!
results.description: Following his return from England, Spider-Man crosses paths with Slyde

results.title: High Stakes
results.description: While vacationing in Atlantic City, Spider-Man encounters the Vulture

results.title: Beware the Stalker from the Stars!
results.description: With the help of the alien Vaalu, Spider-Man keeps a cosmic device from the clutches of the evil Xanja

results.title: Nothing to Fear ...
results.description: Spider-Man gives a crook a second chance

results.title: Scared to Succeed!
results.description: Spider-Man saves an auto executive and his son from Headhunter and the evil corporation E.S.I.

results.title: Torch Bearing
results.description: During the time of the renovation of the Statue of Liberty, Spider-Man follows the Statue's torch to California to retrieve his street clothes and a broken web-shooter and foils an attempt to steal the torch

results.title: Mask
results.description: Wolverine helps Spider-Man overcome his guilt over Ned Leeds' death; the Rose, in attempting to cut his losses following Ned's death, runs afoul of the new Hobgoblin

results.title: Iron Bars Do Not a Prison Make ... or Vulture Is as Vulture Does!
results.description: The Vulture escapes from prison to take revenge on the Vulturions for stealing his designs

results.title: The Wages of Sin
results.description: Spider-Man is still stunned by the revelation that Ned Leeds was the Hobgoblin; Richard Fisk, in confessing his sins to a priest, relates his origin as the Rose and that of Ned as the Hobgoblin

results.title: The Coffin
results.description: Kraven, in order to regain his honor, unveils his master plan to destroy Spider-Man

results.title: Resurrection
results.description: Spider-Man exhumes himself from the grave, reunites with Mary Jane, and sets out to face Kraven in a final showdown

results.title: What's the Matter with Mommy?
results.description: To keep his connection to the underworld a secret, Frank Gibbs commits his wife to the "mad dog ward" of a mental institution; Spider-Man investigates

results.title: Fourth and Eternity
results.description: The Watcher wagers the fate of the universe based on the outcome of a children's football game in which Spider-Man participates

results.title: You Can Go Home Again!
results.description: Peter Parker's return to Midtown High as a substitute teacher is spoiled by an obsessed science student (Steve Petty) and a revamped Living Brain; El Arana prepares to become the new Tarantula

results.title: Phreak-Out!
results.description: A science project gone wrong turns Steve Petty in Phreak; El Arana becomes the second Tarantula; Robbie Robertson learns that Tombstone has returned to New York City

results.title: Moving Up
results.description: Hobgoblin attempts to assassinate an intoxicated Spider-Man

results.title: Petty Crimes
results.description: Spider-Man fights the Looter to recover May and Nathan's stolen engagement ring

results.title: Arms and the Man!
results.description: Spider-Man is unable to stop Doctor Octopus' mechanical arms from breaking him out of imprisonment

results.title: All You Need Is Love
results.description: Spider-Man, investigating Betty Leeds' disappearance, discovers that she has joined a cult called the Students of Love

results.title: That Old-Time Religion
results.description: Spider-Man's attempt to rescue Betty from the Students of Love goes awry; Mary Jane considers modeling lingerie

results.title: Pressure!
results.description: After Spider-Man refuses to free Betty from the Students of Love, Flash does so with the help of de-programmers; Mary Jane poses for lingerie photos

results.title: Autodafe, or ... Nobody Expects the Spanish Inquisition
results.description: Peter Parker, Flash Thompson and Reverend Tolliver de-program Betty Brant Leeds; Mary Jane rethinks her lingerie modeling career after May sees the photos

items.name: Hulk Visionaries: Peter David Vol. 3 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Reunion
results.description: Spider-Man, in Las Vegas for a book signing as Peter Parker, runs afoul of the Hulk and a mercenary group called Warzone.

items.name: Hulk Visionaries: Peter David Vol. 3 (Trade Paperback)
Hulk Visionaries: Peter David Vol. 3 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Death from Above!
results.description: Spider-Man is stranded in the desert when his flight out of Las Vegas is downed by the Vulture

results.title: The Power of ... Hate!
results.description: Spider-Man, in Shriver Cove, Massachusetts for a book signing as Peter Parker, discovers that the entire town has been brainwashed by Nekra

results.title: The Face in the Mirror
results.description: In the midst of Inferno, the Hobgoblin searches for the original Green Goblin formula of Norman Osborn

results.title: Eyes of the Demon
results.description: The demonically-altered Hobgoblin fights Spider-Man in the sewers of a Manhattan

results.title: Corner Business
results.description: Spider-Man targets a pusher selling drugs to Mary Jane's friend Lorraine

results.title: The Enemy Within!
results.description: Practice against a Spider-Man robot cannot prevent Doctor Octopus' pathological fear of Spider-Man from returning when confronted with the real thing

results.title: 1,000 Words
results.description: Spider-Man is labeled a thief by the Daily Bugle after he provides assistance to Silver Sable, leading to a free-for-all with various other heroes; the Chameleon imprisons and impersonates J. Jonah Jameson; the Lobo brothers initiate their revenge against
